      "comment": "WESTERN ACTION (8) put the writing on the wall when runner-up two runs ago then enjoyed the step up to this distance when he came from wider on this row and scored by 2.6 metres. No harm in drawing here with the sprint lane to rely upon. Big chance to back that up. LUKA DONCIC NZ (7) produced a strong effort last time out when runner-up here, beaten a head. Must overcome a very wide draw but will be reaching peak fitness fourth-up so can go one better this time around. ASCOT SHOWTIME (2) draws well and is suited going up to this distance having recorded two wins and a placing from the four times she has attempted it here. ITS BACK PAGE NEWS NZ (1) showed improvement last start. coming from the back row to finish third at Redcliffe. Gets the ace draw and should be race fit fourth up.",
